{"id": "18207", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18207", "title": "Grimoire", "text": "A grimoire is a textbook of &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; typically giving instructions for invoking &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, performing divination, and gaining magical powers.\nWarlock spells.\nSeveral grimoires are actually world drops for spells and not demon minion abilities. Due to the removal of spell ranks in &lt;a href=\"patch%204.0.1\"&gt;patch 4.0.1&lt;/a&gt;, these items are no longer usable, and were converted into &lt;a href=\"Quality%23Poor_Quality_.28Grey.29\"&gt;Poor Quality&lt;/a&gt; vendor items.\nIn addition, three grimoires drop in the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Ahn%27Qiraj\"&gt;Ruins of Ahn'Qiraj&lt;/a&gt; that taught high level versions of the Warlock spells.\nOffhand items.\nSome grimoires are &lt;a href=\"offhand\"&gt;offhand&lt;/a&gt; items:\nQuest items.\nA few grimoires are &lt;a href=\"quest%20item\"&gt;quest item&lt;/a&gt;s:\nWarlock pet grimoires.\nPrior to &lt;a href=\"patch%203.0.2\"&gt;patch 3.0.2&lt;/a&gt;, there were &lt;a href=\"demon%20trainer\"&gt;demon trainer&lt;/a&gt;s that used to sell grimoires. These grimoires could teach a &lt;a href=\"warlock%20minion\"&gt;minion&lt;/a&gt; an ability or spell. Since the patch, all demon abilities and spells will automatically be learned as pets gain levels."}
