{"id": "70355", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=70355", "title": "Gargok", "text": "Gargok is an &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20Gulch\"&gt;Warsong Gulch&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"battlemaster\"&gt;battlemaster&lt;/a&gt; found at the &lt;a href=\"Mor%27shan%20Base%20Camp\"&gt;Mor'shan Base Camp&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Barrens\"&gt;Northern Barrens&lt;/a&gt;. He appears to be the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20Outriders\"&gt;Warsong Outriders&lt;/a&gt;, as he represents them during the ceremony at the &lt;a href=\"Undercity\"&gt;Undercity&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nAs a member of the &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20clan\"&gt;Warsong clan&lt;/a&gt;, he was affiliated with the &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20Outriders\"&gt;Warsong Outriders&lt;/a&gt;, and served as the &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20Gulch\"&gt;Warsong Gulch&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"battlemaster\"&gt;battlemaster&lt;/a&gt; found at the &lt;a href=\"Mor%27shan%20Base%20Camp\"&gt;Mor'shan Base Camp&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Barrens\"&gt;Northern Barrens&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion of the Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, when an &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; reached Prestige Rank 2, Gargok could be found in the &lt;a href=\"Undercity\"&gt;Undercity&lt;/a&gt; alongside other notable leaders of the Horde. He was present at the ceremony hosted by Warchief &lt;a href=\"Sylvanas%20Windrunner\"&gt;Sylvanas Windrunner&lt;/a&gt; that congratulates the adventurer for their battles against the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;, following their receiving of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Warlord%27s%20Medal%20of%20Valor\"&gt;High Warlord's Medal of Valor&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Warchief\"&gt;Warchief&lt;/a&gt;, as well as an artifact appearance.\nAt some unknown point in time after the fall of &lt;a href=\"Garrosh%20Hellscream\"&gt;Garrosh Hellscream&lt;/a&gt;, Gargok reached out to his niece &lt;a href=\"Gorgonna\"&gt;Gorgonna&lt;/a&gt; desiring to make their family whole again. Gorgonna made her way to &lt;a href=\"Ashenvale\"&gt;Ashenvale&lt;/a&gt;, where she discovered that the Warsong had been shattered by what Garrosh had become. As she found a new place to belong, she eventually proved her strength to all of the clan through &lt;a href=\"mak%27gora\"&gt;mak'gora&lt;/a&gt;, and became the clan's new chieftain, where she vowed to never let them lose their honor again. Thus she represented the Warsong at the first &lt;a href=\"Kosh%27harg\"&gt;Kosh'harg&lt;/a&gt; on Azeroth in &lt;a href=\"Razor%20Hill\"&gt;Razor Hill&lt;/a&gt;, with Gargok joining her. He was initially seen standing next to &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Guard%20Torek\"&gt;Blood Guard Torek&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nI am sorry &lt;class&gt;, but you are not seasoned enough yet to enter Warsong Gulch."}
