{"id": "667191", "revid": "27079649", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=667191", "title": "Gargon", "text": "Gargons (also pluralized as gargon) are &lt;a href=\"Stoneborn\"&gt;Stoneborn&lt;/a&gt; creatures found in &lt;a href=\"Revendreth\"&gt;Revendreth&lt;/a&gt;. Chiseled in the image of things that go bump in the night, these vicious quadrupeds prowl the cobblestone streets of Revendreth to maintain order, by fear or force. Gargons are crafted from stone and animated with &lt;a href=\"anima\"&gt;anima&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"venthyr\"&gt;venthyr&lt;/a&gt; use them as guards, pets, hunting companions, and fellow tormenters of &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s. In the rare battles Revendreth has fought, gargons have been used on the front line against ground forces.\nAs a hunter pet.\nGargons are tamable by &lt;a href=\"hunter\"&gt;hunter&lt;/a&gt;s as part of the &lt;a href=\"stone%20hound\"&gt;stone hound&lt;/a&gt; family. In order to tame gargons, hunters must first learn the skill from &lt;a href=\"Gargon%20Training%20Manual\"&gt;Gargon Training Manual&lt;/a&gt;, a guaranteed drop from &lt;a href=\"Huntmaster%20Petrus\"&gt;Huntmaster Petrus&lt;/a&gt; in Revendreth."}
