{"id": "122904", "revid": "49848256", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=122904", "title": "Garments of the Light (Elwynn Forest)", "text": "Objectives.\nFind Guard Roberts and heal his wounds using &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Heal\"&gt;Lesser Heal&lt;/a&gt; (Rank 2). Afterwards, grant him and then return to &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20Josetta\"&gt;Priestess Josetta&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Goldshire\"&gt;Goldshire&lt;/a&gt;. \nDescription.\nNormally I put forth a small challenge to followers of the Light to test their skill. I want to see if they are worthy of wearing their first robes\u2014a sign that the &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20the%20Holy%20Light\"&gt;church&lt;/a&gt; outwardly approves of the &lt;priest/priestess&gt; and supports &lt;him/her&gt;.\nBut this situation is a bit different. One of Goldshire's citizens saw an injured guard near the lake to the east of here. His name is Roberts. Find him, heal him, fortify his body and return here. If you can do that for me, then I will consider your test complete.\nRewards.\nYou will gain:\nProgress.\nAs you may have already learned, our healing magics are vital to the survival of our people in these harsh times--especially to adventurers and heroes who take up arms and magic to fight back so many different threats.\nYou would do well to always remember how important that skill is. That, coupled with Fortitude, make your companions far more capable in battle since they will be able to stand up to a greater number of blows.\nDo not let anyone dismiss how powerful your magics are.\nCompletion.\nExcellent, &lt;name&gt;. With one more healthy guard out there to help the town, we'll be that much safer. I'm glad to see you're already learning to use your abilities wisely. If you feel you are ready for more training at any time, please come back to me. But for now, take this robe. It will let others know that you are one of our order. If you don't want to wear it, that's fine. Later there will be more tests and this robe isn't necessary for those."}
{"id": "31375", "revid": "819614", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31375", "title": "Garments of the Light (quest)", "text": ""}
{"id": "32909", "revid": "49848256", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32909", "title": "Garments of the Moon", "text": "Garments of the Moon is an &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; only &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; quest in &lt;a href=\"Teldrassil\"&gt;Teldrassil&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"night%20elf\"&gt;night elf&lt;/a&gt; starting zone. In this quest, players are sent by &lt;a href=\"Laurna%20Morninglight\"&gt;Laurna Morninglight&lt;/a&gt; the priest trainer to heal and fortify a wounded Sentinel, just south of &lt;a href=\"Dolanaar\"&gt;Dolanaar&lt;/a&gt;. Note that only priests can receive this quest. &lt;a href=\"In%20Favor%20of%20Elune\"&gt;In Favor of Elune&lt;/a&gt; Is not required for this quest, but cannot be completed once this quest is completed.\nObjectives.\nFind &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Shaya\"&gt;Sentinel Shaya&lt;/a&gt; and heal her wounds using &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Heal\"&gt;Lesser Heal&lt;/a&gt; (Rank 2). Afterwards, grant her and then return to &lt;a href=\"Laurna%20Morninglight\"&gt;Laurna Morninglight&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dolanaar\"&gt;Dolanaar&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nI need your help, &lt;name&gt;. I am needed here to train the other students, but you, you can help one of our injured Sentinels just south of &lt;a href=\"Dolanaar\"&gt;Dolanaar&lt;/a&gt;. She was hurt patrolling the town and could use our aid. Her name is Shaya.\nWhen you find her, heal her wounds, and then fortify her body with your spells. This will at least protect her from harm longer if she finds trouble. Return to me here after you've done your duty to &lt;a href=\"Elune\"&gt;Elune&lt;/a&gt;.\nProgress.\nOur spells of Fortify are very powerful, &lt;name&gt;. They allow our companions to take further injury from all types of attacks and survive in situations where they would normally fall. But this is nothing when compared to our abilities to heal. There are no greater healers than a priest\u2014do well to remember that. Your power alone can turn the tides of battle easily.\nCompletion.\nYou have done well and you have served Elune. For that, I thank you.\nPlease, take this robe as a token of my thanks. It signifies you have earned your place among our order. If you wish, wear it with pride, but either way, we will always recognize you as one of our own.\nGo with Elune, &lt;name&gt;, and thank you.\nWalkthrough.\nObtaining this quest.\nYou must be a &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; to obtain this quest. &lt;a href=\"Laurna%20Morninglight\"&gt;Laurna Morninglight&lt;/a&gt; can be found inside the northern building of &lt;a href=\"Dolanaar\"&gt;Dolanaar&lt;/a&gt;. Note that &lt;a href=\"In%20Favor%20of%20Elune\"&gt;In Favor of Elune&lt;/a&gt; is not required to complete this quest, but once this quest is completed, In Favor of Elune can no longer be completed.\nCompleting this quest.\n&lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Shaya\"&gt;Sentinel Shaya&lt;/a&gt; is just south of &lt;a href=\"Dolanaar\"&gt;Dolanaar&lt;/a&gt;. Simply cast &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Heal\"&gt;Lesser Heal&lt;/a&gt; (Rank 2) and then on her, then return to &lt;a href=\"Laurna%20Morninglight\"&gt;Laurna Morninglight&lt;/a&gt; to complete the quest."}
