{"id": "394217", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=394217", "title": "Garona Halforcen (alternate universe)", "text": "Garona Halforcen is a &lt;a href=\"half-orc\"&gt;half-orc&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"half-draenei\"&gt;half-draenei&lt;/a&gt;. She is 's personal spy and assassin. Garona is the result of breeding between an &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"draenei\"&gt;draenei&lt;/a&gt;, most likely in a way similar to how she was conceived in the main timeline. She has been forcibly aged by &lt;a href=\"warlock\"&gt;warlock&lt;/a&gt; magics and spells have been placed on her mind to follow Gul'dan's every order.\nBiography.\nOn the Shadow's Trail.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cordana%20Felsong\"&gt;Cordana Felsong&lt;/a&gt; locate the Shadow Council, Gul'dan escapes before he can be captured. However, he sends Garona after Khadgar, who nearly succeeds in assassinating him but is stopped and fought off by Cordana.\nLegendary Journey.\nGarona's second attack on Khadgar is after the wizard locates Gul'dan via scrying. She successfully poisons him and flees into the lower reaches of &lt;a href=\"Zangarra\"&gt;Zangarra&lt;/a&gt;, only for the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;General&lt;/a&gt; to pursue and capture her. The antidote on Garona's person is used to save Khadgar's life, and with her imprisoned at his tower Khadgar begins searching for a way to break Gul'dan's spells on Garona's mind.\nGarona is eventually freed of Gul'dan's control thanks to Khadgar, Cordana, and the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;General&lt;/a&gt;. She then helped the Archmage and the adventurer to spy on Gul'dan as he took over the Iron Horde and eventually she joins the General's &lt;a href=\"Garrison\"&gt;Garrison&lt;/a&gt; as a Legendary &lt;a href=\"Follower\"&gt;Follower&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuotes.\n&lt;The half-orc snarls at you from within her arcane prison. Her eyes are filled with fire and hate - it's clear that Gul'dan still has her under his complete control.&gt;\nI cannot thank you enough for what you and Khadgar have done for me. I am yours to command."}
{"id": "452461", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=452461", "title": "Garona Halforcen (film universe)", "text": "Garona Halforcen is a &lt;a href=\"half-orc\"&gt;half-orc&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-human\"&gt;half-human&lt;/a&gt; warrior, and respected member of the . Once the slave of the warlock , Garona was freed by , and formed an unexpected alliance with the humans of , fighting alongside them against the Horde. \nWhen the human forces were betrayed by , requested Garona kill him in front of the other orcs, securing the honor of his death for herself, in the hopes of one day bringing peace between their peoples. Her reluctant actions won her freedom and acceptance within the Horde, but at the price of the death of her friend, and her betrayal in the eyes of .\nHistory.\nGarona was born to an orcish woman who had mated with a young , for which the mother was burned alive. The child would have been killed, too, had not intervened, taking the child as a slave. A half-breed, small and weak in comparison to the other orcs, the warlock would give her the name \"\", meaning \"Cursed\". Gul'dan did however also give Garona one of her mother's tusks to remember her by.\nGarona was present when Gul'dan was visited by what he called a \"demon\", later described by her as having a voice \"like fire and ash\", although she did not see its face. The demon taught Gul'dan about the , among other things, making the invasion of Azeroth possible.\nDying Draenor.\nGarona, as Gul'dan's slave, was present when Gul'dan sought to gain the support of the for his and witnessed 's refusal to join.\nGarona accompanied Gul'dan when he approached again, two years later. Although the young chieftain was tempted, he rejected Gul'dan's offer, convinced that accepting would make them the warlock's slaves. In her surprise Garona used the draenei tongue to warn the Frostwolves that Gul'dan was dangerous. (who had learned the tongue in her exile) informed Garona that they knew, and lied to Gul'dan when he demanded to know what had been said, telling them that Garona had called the clan fools for rejecting Gul'dan's offer.\nWarcraft.\nGarona was at her master's side during the preparations for the opening of the .\nVideos.\n&lt;vplayer/&gt;"}
