{"id": "47359", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47359", "title": "Garren's Haunt", "text": "Garren's Haunt is a large &lt;a href=\"Farm\"&gt;farmstead&lt;/a&gt; in the northern part of the &lt;a href=\"Tirisfal%20Glades\"&gt;Tirisfal Glades&lt;/a&gt;. It includes a farmhouse, a barn, a couple of silos, and a wide-stretched field.\nThe &lt;a href=\"darkhound\"&gt;darkhound&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Plague%20%28darkhound%29\"&gt;Plague&lt;/a&gt; can be found in the barn.\nHistory.\nOnce a bountiful place, the farmstead became gray and lifeless due to the effects the &lt;a href=\"Plague%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Plague of Undeath&lt;/a&gt;. Garren and his family were brutally murdered by the &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Scourging%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Scourging of Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;, and his home became residence to the &lt;a href=\"Rot%20Hide\"&gt;Rot Hide&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"gnoll\"&gt;gnoll&lt;/a&gt;s, and their leader &lt;a href=\"Maggot%20Eye\"&gt;Maggot Eye&lt;/a&gt;, who hungrily attacked anyone who came too close.\nFollowing the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, the area saw increased &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; activity and contained several plague tanks. &lt;a href=\"Apothecary%20Jerrod\"&gt;Apothecary Jerrod&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Crispin\"&gt;Apprentice Crispin&lt;/a&gt; sent &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s to perform various tasks, notably to kill &lt;a href=\"Maggot%20Eye\"&gt;Maggot Eye&lt;/a&gt; and his undead &lt;a href=\"gnoll\"&gt;gnoll&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Battle for Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;, the farmstead was abandoned by both the Forsaken and Rot Hide gnolls, and was damaged by the advance of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; forces. Following the end of the conflict, Garren's Haunt remained abandoned. It is unknown what happened to &lt;a href=\"Maggot%20Eye\"&gt;Maggot Eye&lt;/a&gt; and the Rot Hide gnolls, but they were possibly killed either by the Forsaken or the Alliance."}
