{"id": "558684", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=558684", "title": "Azurelight Square", "text": "Azurelight Square is an open air location in southern &lt;a href=\"Eredath\"&gt;Eredath&lt;/a&gt;, between the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Oronaar\"&gt;Ruins of Oronaar&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Conservatory%20of%20the%20Arcane\"&gt;Conservatory of the Arcane&lt;/a&gt;. It features &lt;a href=\"eredar\"&gt;eredar&lt;/a&gt; architecture, however it is now mostly deserted apart from ghosts. There is a concentration of ruined houses in the east of the area. Powerful &lt;a href=\"Argussian%20Vigilant\"&gt;Argussian Vigilant&lt;/a&gt;s, as well as smaller &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Argus%20Construct\"&gt;Ancient Argus Construct&lt;/a&gt;s patrol this region. The wildlife is represented by numerous &lt;a href=\"talbuk\"&gt;talbuk&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"mana%20ray\"&gt;mana ray&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Wrangler%20Kravos\"&gt;Wrangler Kravos&lt;/a&gt; is encountered here.\nSpeculation.\nIt was likely known as (or contained) the &lt;a href=\"Azurelight%20Bazaar\"&gt;Azurelight Bazaar&lt;/a&gt;, a thriving marketplace with all manner of ancient treasure."}
{"id": "69946", "revid": "41585536", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=69946", "title": "Azureload Mine", "text": ""}
{"id": "42962", "revid": "48749411", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42962", "title": "Azurelode Mine", "text": "The Azurelode Mine is a &lt;a href=\"mine\"&gt;mine&lt;/a&gt; in southwestern &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Foothills\"&gt;Hillsbrad Foothills&lt;/a&gt;, south of &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Fields\"&gt;Hillsbrad Fields&lt;/a&gt; and west of what was once &lt;a href=\"Southshore\"&gt;Southshore&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nBefore the &lt;a href=\"Greymane%20Wall\"&gt;Greymane Wall&lt;/a&gt; was built, Azurelode Mine and its surrounding hill were a part of &lt;a href=\"Gilneas%20%28kingdom%29\"&gt;Gilneas&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the time of the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Hillsbrad\"&gt;Battle for Hillsbrad&lt;/a&gt;, it was an &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;-controlled mine. It was a home to miners under &lt;a href=\"Foreman%20Bonds\"&gt;Foreman Bonds&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Fields\"&gt;Hillsbrad Fields&lt;/a&gt;, and had guards to protects the miners. It supplied iron to Alliance armories.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, the mine was taken over by the &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; and became a &lt;a href=\"spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Farm\"&gt;farm&lt;/a&gt; led by &lt;a href=\"Spider-Handler%20Sarus\"&gt;Spider-Handler Sarus&lt;/a&gt;, with &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Keyton\"&gt;Captain Keyton&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dreadguard%20%28NPC%29\"&gt;Dreadguard&lt;/a&gt;s guarding the farm. The remaining humans (&lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Sentry\"&gt;Hillsbrad Sentry&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Foreman\"&gt;Hillsbrad Foreman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Miner\"&gt;Hillsbrad Miner&lt;/a&gt;s) which were not able to escape in time have been paralyzed by the spiders' Paralytic Poison. These humans are being saved until they're needed at the &lt;a href=\"Sludge%20Fields\"&gt;Sludge Fields&lt;/a&gt; to the north. Unfortunately, &lt;a href=\"Dumass\"&gt;Dumass&lt;/a&gt; has also fallen prey to the spiders and must be rescued.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Domesticated%20Mine%20Creeper\"&gt;Domesticated Mine Creeper&lt;/a&gt;s, which have not been fed for days, have begun sampling the humans and refuse commands to stop. The Forsaken can't feed them at the moment due to their \"supplies\" being stolen by the nearby &lt;a href=\"murloc\"&gt;murloc&lt;/a&gt;s, but they also can't leave to gather new supplies as they're afraid the same murlocs will take over the mine as soon as they leave.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, the mine was a battlefield between the Alliance and Horde.\nPre-Cataclysm.\nPrior to Cataclysm, the Horde had three quests that involved this area:"}
