{"id": "659978", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=659978", "title": "BULL-E", "text": "BULL-E is a minigame that can be played on the &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Arcade%20Console\"&gt;Darkmoon Arcade Console&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Faire\"&gt;Darkmoon Faire&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the game is launched, BULL-E the mechanical dog will appear, fall on its side, and stop moving. The goal is to revive the dog by uncrossing its tangled wires, displayed as pink and blue lines. Pink lines represent crossed wires that must be fixed.\nTo leave the game, right-click the BULL-E &lt;a href=\"buff\"&gt;buff&lt;/a&gt;.\nDifficulty.\nBULL-E is a (probably-)unending gauntlet that always begins with the simplest puzzle possible: four vertices connected by four lines. As the player progresses, more vertices and lines are added, gradually turning the circuits from basic shapes into grids of squares or series of concentric circles.\nVery high-level circuits can require a fair amount of trial-and-error to complete, since all the overlapping pink lines make it difficult to see which vertices are connected to each other.\nQuotes.\nThe idea is simple. The game is hard! Uncross the wires to fix poor BULL-E's circuits.\nThere is only one difficulty level: Pretty easy to insane-o hard! Give up and you have to start from the beginning!\n&lt;br&gt;"}
