{"id": "44802", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44802", "title": "Crystal Vale", "text": "The Crystal Vale is a valley in the far northwestern corner of &lt;a href=\"Silithus\"&gt;Silithus&lt;/a&gt;. It is populated by &lt;a href=\"Earth%20elemental\"&gt;earth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"air%20elemental\"&gt;air elemental&lt;/a&gt;s and is a popular location for farming too. It is also the location of the final battle in the &lt;a href=\"%3AThunderfury%2C%20Blessed%20Blade%20of%20the%20Windseeker\"&gt;:Thunderfury, Blessed Blade of the Windseeker&lt;/a&gt; quest chain, with &lt;a href=\"Thunderaan\"&gt;Thunderaan&lt;/a&gt;. One quest in the area is &lt;a href=\"The%20Twilight%20Mystery\"&gt;The Twilight Mystery&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ravaged%20Twilight%20Camp\"&gt;Ravaged Twilight Camp&lt;/a&gt; is located in the vale.\nThe valley is mostly destroyed at the end of the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion of the Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt; alongside the majority of Silithus. &lt;a href=\"Highlord%20Demitrian\"&gt;Highlord Demitrian&lt;/a&gt; continued to stay in the area though.\n&lt;a href=\"Air%20elemental\"&gt;Air&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"earth%20elemental\"&gt;earth elemental&lt;/a&gt;s remain in the area but are chaotic from living in the long shadow of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20of%20Sargeras\"&gt;Sword of Sargeras&lt;/a&gt;. After the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Zekhan\"&gt;Zekhan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rexxar\"&gt;Rexxar&lt;/a&gt; visited the area, and the troll ambassador was able to somewhat soothe those that heeded his calls. The elementals chattered and rumbled with stories about the many pains of Azeroth, from centuries ago to more recent days. The tales made it clear that much shamanic work remains to be done in Silithus.\nIn the RPG.\nApparently not all the &lt;a href=\"Twilight%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Twilight's Hammer&lt;/a&gt; followers are the skilled &lt;a href=\"warlock\"&gt;warlock&lt;/a&gt;s they purport to be. In the &lt;a href=\"Twilight%20Base%20Camp\"&gt;Twilight Base Camp&lt;/a&gt; you can hear a story about this place, where a warlock called Highlord Demitrian got a bit greedy raising crystals. It seems he tried to enslave a powerful air elemental called Thunderaan but got caught himself. Now he and his men serve the wind elemental, searching the area for some talisman."}
