{"id": "161518", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161518", "title": "Ghostlands questing guide", "text": "This questing guide for the zone of Ghostlands details an efficient method to obtain and complete the quests in &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor a list of all Ghostlands quests in a sortable table, see &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands%20quests\"&gt;Ghostlands quests&lt;/a&gt;.\n Note: The questing guides are not meant for power-leveling purposes. Rather, they are meant to show players the most efficient way to complete all quests available for a particular zone. If you know of a better order or method to accomplish this, your input is welcome (in fact, greatly desired). For major changes, feel free to edit, but make a note in the as to your reasoning.\nGhostlands (Level 10 - 20).\n&lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt; is the zone most blood elves will quest in, once they leave from &lt;a href=\"Eversong%20Woods\"&gt;Eversong Woods&lt;/a&gt;. It is also home to the raid instance &lt;a href=\"Zul%27Aman\"&gt;Zul'Aman&lt;/a&gt;. The zone is connected to Eversong Woods in the north and Eastern Plaguelands in the south.\nOther zone options for this level include &lt;a href=\"Barrens\"&gt;Barrens&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Silverpine%20Forest\"&gt;Silverpine Forest&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhere to go from here.\nThe next step for most the players will be the &lt;a href=\"Barrens\"&gt;Barrens&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Hillsbrad%20Foothills\"&gt;Hillsbrad Foothills&lt;/a&gt;. See the &lt;a href=\"Barrens%20questing%20guide\"&gt;Barrens questing guide&lt;/a&gt; for details on preparation and questing in that area."}
{"id": "128511", "revid": "41171629", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=128511", "title": "Ghostlands quests", "text": "This is a list of all &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt; quests in table format.\nFor a questing guide detailing the best order to obtain and complete quests in &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt;, see &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands%20questing%20guide\"&gt;Ghostlands questing guide&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Delivery%20to%20Tranquillien\"&gt;Delivery to Tranquillien&lt;/a&gt; introduces the young &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Elf\"&gt;Blood Elf&lt;/a&gt; players to this region.\nQuest table.\nQuests which require players to leave &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt; are denoted by a . Mouse over the icon to see where the quests take place.\nQuests which are part of a chain are denoted by . Click the downward arrow to the right of the icon to view the chain. \nLake Elrendar.\nIn the center of the lake, on a small island, there is the ghost of &lt;a href=\"Geranis%20Whitemorn\"&gt;Geranis Whitemorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nSuncrown Village.\nJust outside of Suncrown Village is a &lt;a href=\"Dying%20Blood%20Elf\"&gt;Dying Blood Elf&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests by Location.\nQuest starters in &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "666147", "revid": "28055547", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=666147", "title": "Ghostlands storyline", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Ghostlands\"&gt;Ghostlands&lt;/a&gt; is a level 10-60 zone in the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Kingdoms\"&gt;Eastern Kingdoms&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Blood%20elf\"&gt;Blood elf&lt;/a&gt; characters are directed there by their questing experiences in the preceding &lt;a href=\"Eversong%20Woods%20storyline\"&gt;Eversong Woods storyline&lt;/a&gt;.\nCompleting the storylines here grants the achievement &lt;a href=\"Ghostlands%20Quests\"&gt;Ghostlands Quests&lt;/a&gt;.\nIntro (starts in Eversong Woods).\nThe first quest chain that takes you to the Ghostlands actually starts in Eversong Woods. You finish it in Tranquillien, the main quest hub in the zone.\nCitizens of Tranquillien.\nThis part of the achievement requires completing many individual quests, which are unlocked by starting a quest chain that begins at &lt;a href=\"Arcanist%20Vandril\"&gt;Arcanist Vandril&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Tranquillien\"&gt;Tranquillien&lt;/a&gt;.\nCompleting &lt;a href=\"Suncrown%20Village%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Suncrown Village (quest)&lt;/a&gt; unlocks the other quests in Tranquillien. It seems that completing them all is necessary for this part of the achievement.\nIn Classic, Rogues and Warlocks are likely to have the class quests they picked up back in Silvermoon City, and can complete here:\nAlso in Classic, this is where you get an introduction to Flight paths:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Dame%20Auriferous\"&gt;Dame Auriferous&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"High%20Executor%20Mavren\"&gt;High Executor Mavren&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Deathstalker%20Rathiel\"&gt;Deathstalker Rathiel&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Apothecary%20Renzithen\"&gt;Apothecary Renzithen&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Deathstalker%20Maltendis\"&gt;Deathstalker Maltendis&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Magister%20Darenis\"&gt;Magister Darenis&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Rathis%20Tomber\"&gt;Rathis Tomber&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Master%20Chef%20Mouldier\"&gt;Master Chef Mouldier&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Arcanist%20Vandril\"&gt;Arcanist Vandril&lt;/a&gt;, for Mages only:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Wanted%20Poster%20%28Tranquillien%29\"&gt;Wanted Poster (Tranquillien)&lt;/a&gt;:\nThis completes the \"Citizens of Tranquillien\" part of the achievement.\nFarstrider Enclave.\nThis quest chain starts in Tranquillien.\nIn Farstrider Enclave, complete the quests listed below.\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Farstrider%20Solanna\"&gt;Farstrider Solanna&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20Vynna\"&gt;Ranger Vynna&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deathstalker%20Maltendis\"&gt;Deathstalker Maltendis&lt;/a&gt;:\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20Krenn%27an\"&gt;Ranger Krenn'an&lt;/a&gt;:\nIn Classic, Rogues can do their second class quest chain here:\nThis completes the \"Farstrider Enclave\" part of the achievement.\nDar'Khan Drathir.\nThis quest chain is unlocked in Tranquillien after completing &lt;a href=\"Windrunner%20Village%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Windrunner Village (quest)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is no quest specifically directing the player to the next questing zone. Choose a level-appropriate zone from a &lt;a href=\"Warchief%27s%20Command%20Board\"&gt;Warchief's Command Board&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Guide\"&gt;Adventure Guide&lt;/a&gt;.\nSide quests.\nFrom &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Vor%27el\"&gt;Apprentice Vor'el&lt;/a&gt;:"}
