{"id": "22515", "revid": "46446795", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22515", "title": "Giant", "text": "Giants are a type of &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; similar to &lt;a href=\"humanoid\"&gt;humanoid&lt;/a&gt;s, but of the very large sort (above 3 meters or so), and larger than most &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;s. The category includes most &lt;a href=\"semi-intelligent\"&gt;semi-intelligent&lt;/a&gt; and some &lt;a href=\"intelligent\"&gt;intelligent&lt;/a&gt; large humanoids. Most giants are &lt;a href=\"elite\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt;.\nMany of the giants on &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; were created by the &lt;a href=\"Keeper\"&gt;Keeper&lt;/a&gt;s as part of their ordering of Azeroth in the &lt;a href=\"Forge%20of%20Wills\"&gt;Forge of Wills&lt;/a&gt;, meant to protect and oversee the land and ocean. According to &lt;a href=\"Brann%20Bronzebeard\"&gt;Brann Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt;, most of Azeroth's giants were hit with the &lt;a href=\"Curse%20of%20Flesh\"&gt;Curse of Flesh&lt;/a&gt;, but it doesn't seem to have affected them much. Only a handful remain in the most untouched areas of Azeroth, where they are still fulfilling their ancient duties, although some (molten giants and &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Kazum\"&gt;Baron Kazum&lt;/a&gt; for example) seem to serve the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Gods\"&gt;Old Gods&lt;/a&gt; against their will. When &lt;a href=\"Illidan%20Stormrage\"&gt;Illidan Stormrage&lt;/a&gt; threatened the security of the world, &lt;a href=\"archdruid\"&gt;archdruid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Malfurion%20Stormrage\"&gt;Malfurion Stormrage&lt;/a&gt; used his vast powers to call upon the aid of the &lt;a href=\"mountain%20giant\"&gt;mountain giant&lt;/a&gt;s. &lt;a href=\"Kael%27thas%20Sunstrider\"&gt;Kael'thas Sunstrider&lt;/a&gt; ordered the dropping of huge crystals onto &lt;a href=\"Outland\"&gt;Outland&lt;/a&gt;, which summoned giants and corrupted them. This explains why &lt;a href=\"Draenor\"&gt;Draenor&lt;/a&gt;'s giants seek to harm the lands instead of protecting it.\nLanguage.\nDepending on the type of giant, some speak &lt;a href=\"Titan%20%28language%29\"&gt;Titan&lt;/a&gt;, some speak &lt;a href=\"Giant%20%28language%29\"&gt;Giant&lt;/a&gt;, and some speak &lt;a href=\"Kalimag\"&gt;Kalimag&lt;/a&gt;.\nList of giants.\nOthers.\nOther creatures called giants in \"Warcraft\" include:"}
